---
// src/pages/docs/solid/install.astro
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout title="Install & Overview - Solid">
  <div class="mb-4 text-sm font-mono text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-widest">
    @elekcsv/solid
  </div>

  <h1 class="mb-8 border-b-2 border-black pb-4">6.1 Install & Overview</h1>

  <p class="text-xl text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-10">
    The <code>@elekcsv/solid</code> package provides a highly optimized
    <code>useCSVImporter</code> primitive for SolidJS. It wraps the headless
    <code>@elekcsv/core</code> engine and maps importer state directly to Solid
    accessors.
  </p>

  <h2>Installation</h2>
  <p>
    The package is fully UI-agnostic. You get the importer state machine and parsing
    pipeline, then render your own dropzone, table, and review UI with Solid components.
  </p>

  <pre><code>npm install @elekcsv/solid @elekcsv/core
# or
yarn add @elekcsv/solid @elekcsv/core
# or
pnpm add @elekcsv/solid @elekcsv/core</code></pre>

  <h2>Why the Solid Hook?</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-black">Signal-Native Flow:</strong> Importer values like
      <code>step()</code>, <code>isLoading()</code>, and <code>hasErrors()</code> plug
      directly into Solid's fine-grained reactivity model.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-black">Non-Blocking Parsing:</strong> Large CSV files are
      processed asynchronously to keep your UI responsive during parse and validation.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-black">Headless UI Freedom:</strong> Keep complete control
      over the presentation layer while elekcsv handles schema mapping and validation.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mt-16 flex justify-end">
    <a
      href="/docs/solid/basic"
      class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-black text-white rounded-md text-sm font-medium hover:bg-neutral-800 no-underline! transition-colors"
      style="text-decoration:none;"
    >
      Next: Basic Usage
      <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        ><path
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round"
          stroke-width="2"
          d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3"></path>
      </svg>
    </a>
  </div>
</Layout>
